Meanwhile, in Dutch oven, combine remaining ingredients except spaghetti. Cook
over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes. Reduce
heat to low.
Add browned meat.
Cook, stirring occasionally,
until stew is thickened (20 to 30 minutes).
Meanwhile,
cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve stew over spaghetti.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Press meat lightly in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer onion, frozen peas, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place chops in baking dish.
Slice potatoes and onions round; place on top of chops in layers.
Pour sauce on top.
Cover with tinfoil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple and yam bake
directions: Grease a 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix together apple pie filing and sweet potatoes; pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, nutmeg and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, softened butter, desired extract and Eagle Brand milk.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate until firm and cold.

title: spice cake(peppercake)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix baking soda and sour cream first and then add to rest of mixture.
Spray Pam in a loaf pan and put mixture in loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl, layer in order and refrigerate overnight. Mix well before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place meat in a 3-quart casserole and sprinkle generously with seasoned salt.
Mix the cans of Campbell's soup with the meat cubes and then add the remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles, potatoes or rice. Makes 6 generous servings.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar, pecans and coconut in saucepan until butter is melted. Spread in hot pie shell. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: terry's meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all of this well.
Mold into a large loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients, saving nuts and apples for last.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
No need to ice; can eat plain or with whipped topping.

title: ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Form into ball. Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: sugarless fruit freezies
directions: Bring fruit and water to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Add pats of butter and 1/4 teaspoon of salt; set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit mixture.
Bake in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into bars.
These bars freeze well.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl cream sugar, shortening and eggs together and beat until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to the cream mixture.
Crumble and stir in mincemeat.
Drop by round teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on baking sheets that are lightly greased.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: curry and rice
directions: Put meat, onions and potatoes in skillet with oil. Fry. Add salt, tomato puree, tomatoes, curry powder and garlic. Simmer 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and pineapple.
Separately combine Ranch dressing mix with mayonnaise and reserved pineapple juice. Add to chicken mixture and toss well to coat; chill.

title: mexican dip
directions: In glass pie plate, layer beans, meat and onion.
Top with chilies, cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, garnish with guacamole, sour cream and olives.
Serve with corn chips.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients together.
Let cool.
Mix pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice with first mixture and refrigerate until jelled.
Add 2 boxes Dream Whip, prepared as directed.
Remove brown from 2 angel food cakes.
Break in small pieces and line 4-quart bowl with wax paper.
Put handful of mix, then layer of cake.
Keep layering until all is gone.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn out on platter and frost with Dream Whip. Sprinkle with coconut flakes.
Keep refrigerated.

title: five minute chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter in a small bowl.
Add cocoa, blend well. Gradually add sugar alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and ready to spread.

title: six-layer mexican casserole
directions: First Layer:
Place 6 uncooked tortillas on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cook cornstarch and milk until thickens like pudding.
Remove from heat; cool to tepid.
Measure into mixer bowl the oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add slightly warm cornstarch mixture.
Add the vanilla; whip at high speed until it looks like whipped cream.

title: chocolate nut toffee bars
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla, sifted flour and salt.
Spread evenly on a greased 9 x 13-inch (or 10 x 15-inch) baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 180°C (350°).
Melt chocolate and spread while warm onto baked dough. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares or bars while still warm. Makes 25 to 36 pieces.

title: lasagna in a bun
directions: Cut top off of bun.
Hollow out.
Use crumbs for something else, leaving 1/2-inch shells.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients by hand.
Shape mixture around piece of pepperoni, ham, pickle, olive, canned onion, etc.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: susan lappen's crabmeat pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese and
spread it out evenly on a pizza pan, then mix horseradish and ketchup.
Add celery and crabmeat. Spread mixture over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers as a dip.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter; put in casserole. Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over onions; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until golden.

title: best white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Chop nuts and fruits; mix with part of flour and fold into mixture.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together and fold in.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan (paper lined) or small loaf pans.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
(Small loaves may be done in 2 1/2 hours.) This cake keeps well, wrapped and in a tin, for at least two months.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Grate squash on coarse side of grater.
Add salt and allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Form into small patties.
If too moist, roll in flour.
Fry on heavily greased griddle until slightly brown. Serve hot.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about 4 months.
Cook over kerosene fire for approximately 4 weeks or until tender.
Add onions and pepper; cook until tender.

title: baked egg custard
directions: Combine Egg Beaters, sugar and salt.
Stir in scalded milk and vanilla.
Pour into 5 ounce cups.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set cups in a shallow baking pan.
Add boiling water to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, egg, mashed potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sourdough hot cakes
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour 1/4 cup at a time onto a medium hot griddle, lightly greased.
When the top becomes dry looking (in 3 to 4 minutes), turn and cook other side another 3 minutes or until second side is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: prime ribs of beef with au jus
directions: Remove any roast wrappings and wipe surface with paper towel. Peel garlic and cut into narrow slivers with tip of sharp knife. Poke holes all over fatty parts of meat and insert garlic.
Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Put roast, rib side down, in roasting pan.
Place pan on middle rack of preheated 500° oven.
Roast for 30 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and continue to cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours depending on doneness you prefer.
Use a meat thermometer where it will not hit rib bone or fat.

title: raspberry jam cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs, adding eggs one at a time. Add soda to the milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients and add buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix jam in.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans and bake until it tests done.

title: chili beans
directions: Wash and cook beans until tender, about 3 hours.
Just before beans are done, place remaining ingredients in skillet and brown. Add to beans and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: In small bowl combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Mix with a mixer for 1 minute until light. Add butter and continue beating until well blended. Add flour and cocoa, mix well. Stir in nuts and spread in greased square dish. Put in microwave for 6 to 7 minutes. It well look dry, but will spring back quickly.

title: tender pheasant
directions: Flour pheasant.
Brown in butter and oil.
Place in a casserole which can be placed on a burner.
Add broth.
Cook at a slow heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in browning pan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup, 2 tablespoons flour and the broth you cooked the pheasant in.
Add sour cream last.
Do not boil.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve over rice or pasta or potatoes.

title: shrimp and artichoke soup
directions: In a soup pot, melt butter and saut onion until clear.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low until soup begins to thicken.
Serve immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and mix with sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust and bake 45 minutes or until lightly brown at 375°.

title: chocolate drink mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
To use, add 1/2 cup of mixture to one cup hot water. Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine.
Microwave 2 minutes; add chopped nuts and beat until stiff.
Spread onto slightly buttered pan.

title: california hot chicken salad
directions: Place in large bowl the chicken, celery, almonds and pimiento. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, grated onion, salt and pepper; add to bowl and toss gently with a fork.
Place mixture in individual ramekins or a shallow, oiled casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted margarine and sprinkle over salad.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° until heated through and lightly browned; about 30 minutes for a casserole, or 15 minutes in ramekins.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak first 3 ingredients in 2 tablespoons salt water for 1 hour.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and bring to rolling boil. Add squash and onion; bring to rolling boil.
Take off heat.
Stir in peppers and can.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients until blended.
Roll in parsley flakes for color.
Chill overnight.
Makes 2 balls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, water and sugar 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over jello and stir. Let cool, but not set. Add remaining ingredients and let set.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, cocoa (or spices), soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour alternating with buttermilk.
Bake at 325° until done, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fettuccine, ham and cantaloupe salad
directions: *May be feta cheese with tomato and basil, if you like.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Trim fat from meat, save big pieces to render out for drippings.
Using a very sharp knife, cut meat across grain in slices 1/8 to 1/16-inch thick.
(If slices are large, halve or quarter them to make them bite size pieces.)
Cut white onions into eighths.
Slice green onions lengthwise, then cut crosswise in 1 1/2 inch strips.
Slice the mushrooms lengthwise, stems too, in pieces 1/8 inch thick.
Wash spinach, remove stems and cut large leaves in half.
Mix together in a pitcher, soy, bouillon cube which has been dissolved in the 1/2 cup water, m.s.g., sugar and salt.

title: turkey salad pocket sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Can be covered and refrigerated for several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Use as sandwich filling for pita bread or your favorite sandwich bread.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 25 minutes.

title: chew bread 1
directions: Cream all ingredients together and spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: three bean chili
directions: Warm oil and seasonings in 4 quart pot.
Add peppers and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and all beans and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water or juice as needed.
Season with salt and pepper. Add cilantro or parsley. Garnish with shredded cheese.

title: microwave chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken in microwave for 10 minutes, rotating dish 5 to 10 minutes (High).
Cut meat off bone.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add to meat in casserole dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Heat 4 minutes (High).
Before serving warm, add sour cream and Parmesan cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Refrigerate immediately overnight.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: make ahead hot chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Boil chicken; bone and chop.
Add mayonnaise, onion, mushrooms and eggs.
Butter 6 slices of bread.
Put buttered side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bread with chicken mixture.
Toast remaining 6 slices of bread and place on top of salad.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread on top of toast; sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry tea loaf
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
When batter is prepared, gently fold in blueberries, nuts, raisins and spices.
Pour
mixture into loaf pan, either 3 small or 1 large. Bake
according
to
package
directions,
allowing 10 minutes less
baking
time.
Turn
out on rack and cool.

title: peter pan peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir in Peter Pan.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Shape 1 teaspoon of dough and mash crisscross with fork.
Bake 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into matchstick slices.
Pour rest of ingredients over apples and mix.

title: venison shish kabob marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
This makes about 3 1/2 cup.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Make in a 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream burritos
directions: Soak tortillas in Pace.
Brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix (no water) until meat is well coated.
Shake off picante from each tortilla.
Layer with beans, meat and sour cream.
Roll and place fold side down in baking dish.
Cover burritos with excess picante and grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: sweet and sour appetizers
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients (vinegar, pineapple juice and water), brown sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to boil over low heat until the mixture thickens.
Add browned, chopped sausage, green peppers and pineapple.
Serve with toothpicks, so that the guests may poke a sausage or pineapple chunk.
I usually put this in a crock-pot to keep warm at parties. It is always a hit.

title: elou's pot de creme
directions: Blend in blender, pour in small cups and chill for a couple of hours.
Garnish with whipped cream if you wish.

title: banana waffles
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Pour batter from cup or pitcher onto center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops.
Remove waffle carefully.
Makes three 9-inch waffles.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a flat dish; spread sour cream on top of beans.
Cut up tomato and shred lettuce.
Put on top of sour cream.
Spread salsa and top with shredded cheese.
Use as a dip for chips.

title: stuffed portobellos(low carb)
directions: Crumble sausage and cook until done. Set aside.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
In a medium bowl, combine pasta and all other ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan cups
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add flour and mix with fork or pastry blender.
Form into 1 inch balls, flatten and carefully press into 2 small greased muffin pans.
Mix brown sugar, pecans, egg, melted butter and vanilla to make filling.
Fill pastry cups with filling, being careful not to overfill.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes; cup should then easily lift out of tins.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: easy but elegant chicken crepes
directions: Combine all together in a saucepan; heat thoroughly.
Fill each crepe with a heaping 1/3 cupful.
Fold 2 sides over filling. Place crepes in buttered baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick pot pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bottom of pie shell, except, only use half of gravy and reserve half.
Cover with top pie shell and prick 6 or 8 slits on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour or until golden brown.
Heat remaining gravy and serve over serving slice.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all and cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until lumps together.
Knead with a small amount of flour.
Keeps in the refrigerator for a long time.

title: sauteed chicken strips
directions: In large heavy skillet over medium-high heat, cook butter until bubbly and begins to brown.
Add marinated chicken strips. Saute about 4 minutes or just until opaque throughout and lightly golden.
Fold in parsley and chives.
Immediately remove to warm serving plate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Let stand.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Beat in date mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add together.
Pour in well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Put shortening in skillet; heat and add hamburger.
Brown hamburger.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Turn down heat.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve piping hot in bowls with crisp crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: individual chicken pot pies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the Basic Chicken Stock, bay leaf, peppercorns and the parsley and thyme sprigs and bring to a boil. Add the chicken breasts and simmer until just cooked through, about 20 minutes.
Transfer the chicken to a plate.
Strain the stock, return it to the saucepan and bring to a boil.

title: vegetable curry
directions: Place vegetables on a large plate.
Sprinkle with mixed spices and salt.
Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Saute the onions and garlic.
Add the spiced veggies and stock.
Cover and bring to a boil, simmer for about 20 minutes until all vegetables are tender. Serve with hot cooked rice.
Enjoy!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy peanut bark
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave at 50% power.
Add peanut butter. Mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let set.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Add sugar.
Mix together.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 300°. Roll dough by hand into little balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: shrimp stuffed red peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; cut out stems, seeds and pulp. Drop into boiling salted water and cook, uncovered, for 4 minutes; remove and turn cut side down to drain.

title: corn oysters
directions: Grate corn.
Add eggs, cracker crumbs and flour, sifted with salt, pepper and baking powder.
Drop from a tablespoon into one inch of salad oil (hot enough to brown bread cube), 40 seconds; turn once.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chill shrimp; reserve a few nice shrimp and toss the remainder with celery, eggs, macaroni and pickle.
Combine lemon juice, mayonnaise, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Toss with shrimp mixture.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with reserved shrimp and additional egg (if desired).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Coat a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cut 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick lengthwise slice from each zucchini. Chop the slices and reserve.
Using a melon baller or small spoon and starting from cut side, scoop out most of flesh from each zucchini, leaving a shell. Chop together the flesh and add the reserved chopped slices.
Reserve the zucchini "boats."

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Drain and put in crockpot.
Add the corn, hominy, pinto beans, red kidney beans, tomatoes and green chili, chopped tomatoes.
(DO NOT DRAIN THE VEGETABLES.)
Just open and dump in.
Add ranch dressing mix (dry), the taco seasoning (dry).
Stir together and cook at least 2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Drain juice off fruit.
Beat eggs and mix
all
together.
Pour in greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Prepare Ginger Dressing.
Heat 1-inch oil in Dutch oven to 425°.
Fry 1/4 of the noodles at a time, turning once, until puffed, about 5 seconds.
Drain.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven or saucepot, heat oil and brown 1/2 of chicken.
Remove chicken.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Return chicken to Dutch oven.
Stir in carrots, celery, onion, potatoes and salt.
Mix Lipton soup mix with water and apple juice; pour mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Bring to a boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes, until done and vegetables are tender.

title: turbot fish
directions: Spray skillet with olive oil. Place fish in skillet.
Sprinkle seasoning on fish. Saute slowly until tender.

title: peanut butter pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Then add dry ingredients that have been sifted together; mix well. Dough will be quite stiff.
Roll out on floured area.
Cover dough with layer of peanut butter and then roll in pinwheel fashion.
Wrap waxed paper and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Slice and bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Use immediately or cool and refrigerate.

title: lemon lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple, drained, reserving liquid and add water to make the 1 cup pineapple juice. Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend sour cream with mayonnaise.
Add to mixture.
Pour into oiled salad mold.
Sets up quickly.
Chopped walnuts or maraschino cherries or both may be added.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust and chill 4 hours.

title: summer pizza
directions: Spread bread stick dough flat on cookie sheet.
Bake.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise together and spread over baked bread sticks.
Grate raw veggies (of your choice) and spread/sprinkle on cream cheese.
Cut in squares.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
I put in 2 dishes and freeze one.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: grilled roast
directions: Pour garlic, onion powder and black pepper on wax paper and roll washed and clean roast in mixture.
Wrap in oil and place on grill for 1 hour.

title: drop ginettis
directions: Beat eggs real well (10 minutes).
Add next 4 ingredients. Mix well.
Add baking powder and flour; mix well.
Flour lightly cookie sheet (one time only).
Drop cookies by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter roundup cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and peanut butter, mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Press a crisscross on each cookie.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poor man's dessert
directions: Mix by hand the first 4 ingredients.
Fold in the Cool Whip to the mixture.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 5 things together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Pour melted margarine over then sprinkle pecans over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip, hot or cold.

title: grandpa's tasty codfish
directions: Soak codfish overnight.
Drain water.
Replace with fresh water and boil.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Cook onions, scallions and peppers together in frying pan, then mix codfish, potatoes, onions, scallions, peppers and eggs all together.
Once all ingredients are mixed, make small balls and roll in flour.
In a frying pan pour oil and heat until hot.
Put in six "cake balls" in frying pan with oil until brown all over.
Repeat.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare sugar cookie mix according to directions.
Press on pizza pan with hands (not too thick).
Bake as directed.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Spread on cooled crust.
Layer fruit over topping in circles.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Rinse and dry corned beef; trim off excess fat.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with cold water; put on high heat.
Add salt pork and peppercorns; cover and bring to a boil.
When boiling, lower heat and gently simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and flour; add fruit cocktail and beat.
Pour in buttered oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cover with melted butter.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower mountain
directions: Clean and remove green stem of whole head of cauliflower.
Put in 8-inch glass pie plate, stem end down.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 7 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and dry mustard in bowl.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over top of cooked cauliflower.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Microwave at High 1 minute to melt cheese.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Combine milk and ground beef; mix well.
Divide into 5 patties and place onto sheet of waxed paper.
Pat and mold patties into rounds 6-inches diameter.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty. Fold/draw meat over stuffing and seal edges.
Place into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine and mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat bundles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato-basil soup
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover; process until smooth. Transfer mixture to a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Melt margarine in a small heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually stir sauce mixture into tomato mixture.
Cook over medium heat just until thoroughly heated (do not boil). Ladle soup into individual bowls.
Garnish with fresh basil sprigs, if desired.
Yields 6 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Grease a small casserole dish or 8-inch cake pan.
Layer chicken, Veg-All and soup in casserole dish.
Mix margarine, flour and milk.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Pour pie filling into large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, folding in Cool Whip last.
Let set 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and well mixed.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy mints
directions: Combine water and butter. Place over low heat until butter melts. Remove from heat; add salt and peppermint extract. Gradually add sugar and blend until desired consistency. You can use powdered sugar to roll the mints out for cutting or you can use a candy mold.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat mixture into bottom of well greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly, then beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jellyroll pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool pan on wire rack.

title: christmas punch
directions: For red punch, use cherry Kool-Aid.
For green punch, use lime Kool-Aid.

title: village salad(horiatiki)
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Place in salad bowl with next 5 ingredients.
Season to taste with oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over the dressing and toss.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter, saute vegetables for about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour; add stock.
Bring to boil and simmer 25 minutes.
Put mixture in food processor and put back in pot.
Heat gently adding cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt, shortening and stir until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Stir in flour and mix until all is well blended.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead well, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased pan, covered with a cloth, for 1 hour over a pan of warm (not hot) water and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead down again; place over warm water again for about 30 minutes.
Mold into desired shape.
Let rise for about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done. Yields about 24 large or 36 small rolls or 2 loaves.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until done and tender, about 25 minutes.
Remove from pot.
Reserve broth.
Cook shell and curly pasta in the chicken broth.
Drain pasta.
Add chicken, cucumbers, pepper and green onions.
Season with salt, pepper and Accent.
Add mayonnaise and stir well.
Tastes best when chilled.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender.
Remove and cool enough to handle (or cook the night before).
Chop.
In 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, arrange broccoli.
Lay chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, milk and mayonnaise and stir until smooth.
Add cheese and lemon juice.
Pour sauce over chicken and broccoli and cover chicken completely.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle crumbs on top before serving.

title: broccoli and corn bread casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
pour
in greased casserole. Size depends on how thick you like.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: smothered chops with bacon bits
directions: Stir together 1/3 cup flour the salt and pepper in shallow dish.
Coat pork chop with flour mixture, shaking off excess.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium high heat.
Cook pork chops in oil about 10 minutes turning once, until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Stir onion into dripping in skillet.
Cook about 2 minutes stirring frequently, until softened.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Cook 2 minutes stirring constantly; stir in half and half and bacon bits.
Return pork chops to skillet.
Cover and cook over medium low heat about 30 minutes stirring occasionally, until pork is tender and slightly pink.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Parboil onions about 15 minutes and drain.
Mix meat, salt, pepper, shortening and catsup.
Remove centers of onions and fill with meat mixture.
Arrange in baking dish; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; sprinkle tops with crumbs.
Dot with shortening and bake until brown.

title: egg sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Stir in milk.
Add bread cubes, cheese and sausage. Refrigerate 12 hours in glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deli chicken
directions: In skillet, cook onion.
Add carrots, potatoes and 1 cup broth.
Cover, simmer until tender (about 25 minutes), add more broth if needed.
Cut chicken in quarters; add 5 minutes before end of cooking time.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in pan and keep refrigerated.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Bake turkey at 350° for 4 hours.
Remove turkey from broth. Set aside.
Crumble biscuits, cornbread and crackers in large bowl.
Add sage, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to bread mixture.
Add broth until of desired consistency.
Spray bottom of casserole dish with Pam. Bake at 250° for approximately 35 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In
a large boiler put first 7 ingredients.
Cook until vegetables	are tender.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Drain.
Add
to
chicken mixture and stir well.
Then add cheese
and
more	broth, if needed.
Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar and sugar in a heavy saucepan until thick. Cool completely.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer Cool Whip mixture, sliced bananas and peanuts.
Chill well before serving.

title: corn souffle
directions: Pour corn into buttered casserole. Add flour, sugar and salt. Blend with fork. Add eggs and blend. Add milk and blend well. Top with broken pieces of butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: roman chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil in frying pan.
Place chicken in 6-quart covered, stove-top casserole.
Saute garlic in frying pan until softened; deglaze with wine and add to casserole.
Add bouillon, bacon, tomatoes and marjoram.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts and simmer for 10 minutes.
Skim off any fat from the surface.
Combine flour and butter to form a roux and cook in a small saucepan for 2 minutes, stirring until smooth and blended.
Add roux to chicken and heat a few minutes. Add pepper as desired.

title: spiced tea
directions: Brew tea.
While hot, add cinnamon, nutmeg, almond extract and ground cloves.
Let stand 30 minutes until spices have dissolved. Add rest of water.
Chill.
Serve over ice.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.
